## Features

- Add new thoughts with a simple input form.
- Thoughts automatically disappear after 15 seconds, creating a transient experience.
- Remove individual thoughts by clicking on a remove button.

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

Before running the Passing Thoughts application, ensure you have the following installed:

- Node.js and npm (Node Package Manager)

### Installation

1. Clone the repository to your local machine:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/passing-thoughts.git
   ```

2. Navigate to the project directory:

   ```bash
   cd passing-thoughts
   ```

3. Install dependencies:

   ```bash
   npm install
   ```

## Usage

To start the Passing Thoughts application, run the following command:

```bash
npm start
```

This will launch the application in your default web browser.

## Components

The Passing Thoughts application consists of the following main components:

### AddThoughtForm

A form component that allows users to input new thoughts. Thoughts can be added by typing in the input field and pressing the "Add" button.

### App

The main application component that manages the state of thoughts. It includes the `AddThoughtForm` component and a list of `Thought` components.

### Thought

Represents an individual thought in the list. Each thought includes a text message and a remove button. Thoughts automatically disappear after 15 seconds.

## Utilities

The `utilities` module provides two utility functions used in the application:

- `generateId`: Generates unique IDs for thoughts.
- `getNewExpirationTime`: Calculates the expiration time for a new thought.

